name: CASIO G-Shock GA-2100-1A1ER
description: The new Casio G-Shock GA-2100 series is available in an unusually thin design - only 11.8 mm thick. The octagonal body stands out from the range of “jishocks”, but in fact this is a reference to the very first shockproof model released in 1983 - the Casio DW-5000C. Specifications of the model GA-2100-1A1ER: Movement: quartz Case material: carbon fiber and polymer Glass: mineral. Illumination: automatic double LED illumination and luminescent coating on the hands.

name: ORIS AQUIS CALIBRE 400 01 400 7763 4135-07 8 24 09PEB
description: The men's Oris AQUIS 01 400 7763 4135-07 8 24 09PEB is powered by the new in-house Oris caliber 400 with an impressive power reserve of 120 hours (5 days). Caliber diameter 30 mm. The Oris 400 caliber is anti-magnetic - over 30 parts of the Oris 400 are made from non-ferrous or non-magnetic alloys, so this movement outperforms the increased values defined by the ISO 764 standard in terms of counteracting the influence of a magnetic field on the accuracy of the movement. The manufacturer also gives 10- summer warranty

name: CASIO G-Shock GA-100-1A1ER
description: Type: Men's / Movement: Quartz (battery) / Water resistance: 200 m / Fastening type: Belt / Glass: Mineral

name: ORIS BIG CROWN OKAVANGO AIR RESCUE LIMITED EDITION 01 751 7761 4187-Set
description: Oris is celebrating the 10th anniversary of Botswana's Okavango Air Rescue with a new Okavango Air Rescue Limited with a special textured dial. Okavango Air Rescue, founded in 2011 by Swiss entrepreneur Christian Gross and German Dr. Mischa S. Kruk, is designed to serve Botswana, which is sparsely populated with many remote communities. The watch itself is based on the Big Crown ProPilot, but its main feature is a green dial with a texture reminiscent of the grasses of the Okavango Delta. The set also includes a special box, a certificate, an additional leather strap.

name: ORIS DIVERS SIXTY-FIVE 01 733 7720 4057-07 8 21 18
description: Oris dives back into its history with the Oris Divers Sixty-Five, a vintage reissue of the iconic diving watch that first appeared in the Oris collection 50 years ago. The new Oris Divers Sixty-Five watch inherits the retro design of the original model from the 1960s, but its construction has been seriously modernized using the technologies of 21st century watchmaking. The watch glass, which is shaped like the plastic glass of the vintage prototype, is now made of sapphire glass, which is almost impossible to scratch. In addition, an anti-reflective coating is applied to the inner surface of the glass, which reduces the reflection of light from it and improves the clarity of the dial under water.
